article.description: Jordan Robertson had 21 points, Jordan Swopshire had 10 of his 14 points in the first half and Colgate beat Division III Utica 90-68 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Colgate beats Division III Utica 90-68
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- Jordan Robertson had 21 points, Jordan Swopshire had 10 of his 14 points in the first half and Colgate beat Division III Utica 90-68 on Thursday night. Robertson was 3 of 4 and Swopshire 2 of 2 from 3-point range in the first half. Colgate (3-6) shot 12 of 22 from distance to power a 51-23 lead at the break. The Raiders maintained a comfortable lead throughout the second half. Utica got no closer than 18 points in the final three minutes. Austin Tillotson had 12 points, Alex Ramon scored 11 and Sean O'Brien 10 for Colgate, which built a 35-21 lead and closed the first half on an 18-2 run. Robert Tutein had three 3-pointers and 20 points for Utica. Ivan Iton added 15 points and Jonathan Wilson scored 10.
